<article id="post-37" class="post-37 page type-page status-publish hentry">
	<header class="entry-header">
		<h1 class="entry-title">Senior RESTful Service Engineer (Python)</h1>
	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<div class="entry-content">
		<p dir="ltr">We are a top-notch team of statisticians, data analysts, and engineers with proven experience in delivering fast, accurate, compelling insights from large datasets. We’re building on that experience to create a collaborative platform for advanced analytics in the cloud: Crunch.io.</p>
<p>As Senior RESTful Service Engineer at Crunch.io, you will lead the development of our platform’s public API, as well as the business logic that sits behind it. You will also collaborate in the design of our web application&#8211;the API’s first client&#8211;which provides a friendly environment for data exploration, modeling, and interactive graphics. You will have the opportunity to shape the application’s design from the early stages, putting us on a solid foundation for rapid growth. By doing so, you and your teammates will transform the way people think about exploring and analyzing data.</p>
<p>This position is right for you if:</p>
<ul>
<li dir="ltr">You have at least 8 years of serious programming experience, and at least 4 using Python. By “serious”, we mean applications with complex logic, heavy usage, and no tolerance for errors.</li>
<li dir="ltr">You don’t just speak HTTP fluently: you’re often mistaken for a native speaker. You know that HTTP is a complete application protocol designed to enable massively scalable interoperation; it’s more than just a transport for HTML.</li>
<li dir="ltr">You’ve built APIs before, including but perhaps not exclusively RESTful ones, that have served many types of client applications. Your friends are probably tired of hearing you talk about how superior RESTful services are. (Don’t worry, we’ll never tire of it.)</li>
<li dir="ltr">You believe that test coverage is just as important as the feature set is as a metric of success, and you hold your team to the same standard.</li>
<li dir="ltr">You’ve worked with CherryPy and aren’t afraid to dive into _cptools. No CherryPy experience? Having worked with Flask, web2py, Tornado, Werkzeug, Bottle, or circuits.web may help.</li>
<li dir="ltr">You can provide examples of your work that demonstrate all of the above.</li>
<li dir="ltr">You have strong oral and written communication skills and believe that an idea that can’t be expressed clearly to your peers isn’t yet a good idea.</li>
<li dir="ltr">You have a degree in computer science or related field. Don’t have a CS degree? Use your strong communication skills to sell us on how great your many years of experience are.</li>
<li dir="ltr">You’re looking for a full-time job, not a freelance gig, and you thrive on the intensity and energy that can only come from working with talented peers in a startup environment.</li>
<li dir="ltr">You’re comfortable working on a distributed team. We’re based in the San Francisco Bay Area, but that doesn’t mean you need to be: most of our team live and work elsewhere, in fact. Being located somewhere in the Western Hemisphere with a robust internet connection is helpful, though.</li>
</ul>
<p>To apply, send your resume to neal@crunch.io.</p>
